M|MECH|tx|---
M|TRIP|tx|The same psychological lever cannot be the PRIMARY driver for more than
M|TRIP|tx|3 consecutive pieces of cn on the same br surface.
M|TRIP|Trac|`LEVER_TRACKER.md` per br per surface.
M|TRIP|**Wh|** Audiences adapt. Repeated activation of the same lever produces
M|TRIP|tx|diminishing psychological returns. By the 4th repetition, the audience
M|TRIP|tx|has learned to filter it — it becomes invisible. Variety maintains
M|TRIP|tx|psychological freshness and prevents the br from becoming predictable.
M|TRIP|**Wh|**
M|TRIP|tx|Same Cialdini principle, same layer, same core mechanism.
M|TRIP|tx|Evolving execution (different cp, visual, format) does NOT reset the cap.
M|TRIP|tx|Only switching the PRIMARY lever resets it.
M|TRIP|**Ca|**
M|TRIP|tx|Using a different primary lever once resets the previous lever's count.
M|TRIP|**Ov|**
M|TRIP|tx|No override. The Triple Cap Rule is absolute.
M|TRIP|tx|Even if a lever is performing well — after 3 consecutive uses, switch.
M|TRIP|tx|The goal is long-term br health, not short-term metric op.
M|TRIP|tx|---
M|TRIP|tx|*Variant B is the full st instrument. For fast, hi-frequency cn
M|TRIP|work|
M|TRIP|tx|hi-stakes or first-time cn → Variant B.
M|TRIP|tx|Recurring or quick-turnaround cn → Variant A.*
